A man was yesterday shot dead in Taita-Taveta County for critically injuring three police officers.  The officers were stabbed, and were yesterday receiving treatment at a local hospital.  County Police commander Patrick Okeri said: “We are still piecing up details.”  The officers had raided Mpizinyi village in the outskirts of Mwatate town to arrest the man. “The suspect escaped to his parents’ house near Kipusi Primary,” said an officer.  He was later found sitting with his mother, and turned violent on seeing the officers. The officers said the suspect later emerged from the house armed with a machete, and holding his mother as a shield... attacked the officers. In the process he was shot dead.  Next year’s election outlook gloomy over police meddling  Kenyan troops back from South Sudan mission  Teacher’s 35-hour ordeal with kidnappers on Eldoret highway  Two cops face murder charge over death of man, 20, in police cell     Wakazi Kajiado wahimizwa kula matunda, Ukataji miti Taita Taveta, Yuko wapi Nkatha? | MBIU YA KTN  Police detain a couple and their son for allegedly beating their 15-year-old daughter to death  Jinxed Station? Uproar over Kiptagich Police Station cited for poor relations with the public By Philip Mwakio | 11 hours ago By Renson Mnyamwezi | 11 hours ago By Weldon Kipkemoi | 1 day ago By Brian Okoth | 2 days ago